  "steps": [
    "Dissolve 6.06g Tris Base in 800 mL MilliQ water undetermined It can be made either way depending on what you have available in the lab. Some find it easier to use stock solutions, but it is not necessary as long as final pH is adjusted. Tris Base Fisher Scientific Catalog #BP152-1",
    "Add 3.72g EDTA disodium salt, dihydrate to the 800 mL Tris base and stir to dissolve undetermined EDTA, disodium salt, dihydrate Fisher Scientific Catalog #S312-500",
    "Adjust the pH to 8.0 with HCl",
    "Adjust the volume to 1 liter with MilliQ water",
    "Add 100mg RNase A per liter of buffer P1 undetermined"
